<TITLE> Committee recommends commission to check soaring prices </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 11 (bdnews24.com)  The ministerial committee on the prices of daily essentials Sunday recommended the formation of a permanent commission to rein in soaring prices, an official said. The committee also asked the government to fast-track the final approval and implementation of the Consumer Rights Protection Ordinance 2007, which was okayed by a cabinet meeting in principle. The recommendations came from a meeting of the committee, chaired by commerce ministry additional secretary Golam Mostakim. "The meeting also stressed strengthening activities of mobile courts to ensure quality of products," Mostakim told bdnews24.com after the meeting. The meeting also decided to intensify market monitoring and increase production of products locally, Golam Mostakim added. "Prices of daily essentials except dry chili, turmeric and salt went up. Price of ginger went down by 11.11 percent." The meeting said the prices of soybean oil increased by 13 percent, potato by 10 percent, onion by 20.45 percent, sugar by 7.14 percent and egg by 16.67 percent in November from a month ago, another government official who attended the meeting said. Besides, prices of powdered milk rose by up to 13.5 percent. The meeting also discussed the stock of products, supplies and prices. bdnews24.c
